acknowledgements=a short text at the beginning or end of a book where the writer names people or other works that have helped in writing the book
appendices=a separate part at the end of a book or magazine which gives extra information (plural form)
axes=a line at the side or bottom of a graph (plural form)
democratic=following or supporting the political system of 'the belief in freedom and equality between people'
exploit=to not pay or reward someone enough for something
formulae=a set of letters, numbers or symbols that are used to express a mathematical or scientific rule (plural form)
incentive=something that encourages you to act in a particular way
literature survey=a description of books, articles, essays etc that have been written on a subject
lower-tier grade=a less important level in an organisation or place of work
middle management=the people within a company who are in charge of departments or groups, but who are below those in charge of the whole company
motivation=the need or reason for doing something
negotiate=to try to make or change an agreement by discussion
outnumber=to be greater in number than someone or something
participant=someone who is involved in an activity
pervasive=present or noticeable in every part of a thing or place
pilot study=a piece of work or research that is used to test how good it is before introducing it properly
progress=to improve or develop in skills, knowledge, etc
progress=development and improvement of skills, knowledge, etc
tier=(in a place of work) one of several levels
transcribe=to make a written record of something you hear, such as speech or music
undergo=to experience something, especially a change or medical treatment
undertake=to start work on something that will take a long time or be difficult
upper-tier grade=an important position in a company or other place of work
